The third form electric organ discharge of electric eels - Jun Xu 2021 (read on 11.06.25)
- used electric eel pulses to electroporize(?) GFP DNA into 6dpf zebrafish larvae
- gene transfer not successful w younger larvae or onecelled organisms, only in somatic cells
- claim that electric eel shocks facilitate lateral gene transfer of eDNA to small organisms thereby ecological relevance
- gene transfer was not congenital so questionable theory but cool paper


